external_knowledge:
- 'Epicenters of the storm' refers to regions with the highest number of confirmed COVID-19 cases;
- 'Waves of COVID-19 cases have surged the highest' means the regions have the most significant number of cases;
- The time frame is from January 1, 2023, to December 31, 2023.

- 'Top 5 regions by population density' refers to the regions with the highest population density values;
- 'Latest counts of confirmed COVID-19 cases' refers to the most recent data available for each region;
- '2023' is the specific year for which the population statistics are considered.

- 'Influenza' is a common respiratory illness that can cause significant mortality;
- 'Data quality rating' is a measure of the reliability and accuracy of the data, with higher ratings indicating better quality;
- '2023' is the year in which the data was recorded.

- "Case Fatality Rate (CFR)" is the proportion of deaths among confirmed cases of a disease;
- "High-quality data sources" are those with a data quality rating of 4 or higher;
- "Past six months" refers to data recorded within the last 180 days.

- 'Dense population of over 100 per unit area' refers to an average population density greater than 100;
- 'Vaccination efforts' refer to the average value of the health indicator 'Vaccination Rate';
- 'The vast garden of Asia' is a metaphorical reference to the continent of Asia.

sql:
SELECT SUM(population) AS total_population
FROM population_statistics
WHERE year = 2023;

